    "longBusinessSummary": "Nam A Commercial Joint Stock Bank provides banking products and services in Vietnam. The company mobilizes short, medium, and long-term funds in the form of term and demand deposits, and certificate of deposit; investment and development funds and borrowings from other financial institutions; grants short, medium, and long-term loans; discounts commercial notes, bonds, and valuable papers; and contributes capital, as well as invests in joint ventures. It also provides settlement services; trades in foreign currencies and gold; international payment, overseas duns, and other banking services; cash management, banking, and financial consultancy; leases cabinets and safes; entrustment loans; and acts as an insurance agency. In addition, the company engages in conducting debt factoring activities; preservation of assets; buying and selling of government and corporate bonds; credit granting under bank guarantee; debt purchasing; trading and provision of foreign exchange services on domestic and international market; and lease of office. Nam A Commercial Joint Stock Bank was incorporated in 1992 and is based in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam.",
